WebPie is a pie menu for web pages. Its appearance is very similar to PieDock.
Image and animation quality depend heavily on client and platform.

How to use:

Place both files somewhere in your web project and add those two lines to
the <head/> element of your web page:

<script type="text/javascript"
	src="path/to/WebPieIcon.js"></script>
<script type="text/javascript"
	src="path/to/WebPie.js"></script>

Next you'll have to set up the menu, for example:

<script type="text/javascript">
<!--

var p = new WebPie( {
	icons: [
		new WebPieIcon(
			"path/to/icon.png",
			function(){ alert( "First" ); } ),
		new WebPieIcon(
			"path/to/icon.png",
			function(){ alert( "Second" ); } ),
		new WebPieIcon(
			"path/to/icon.png",
			function(){ alert( "Third" ); } )
		] } );

p.create();

-->
</script>

For more information browse the script files or visit:

http://markusfisch.de/WebPie
